        "created_at": "2026-02-07T16:02:29.233Z",
        "cooked": "<h1><a name=\"p-284183-problem-if-you-want-to-quickly-clean-up-sensitive-messages-either-sent-with-disappearing-messages-or-not-your-only-option-at-the-moment-is-to-manually-delete-individual-messages-or-delete-the-entire-thread-if-your-phone-is-inspected-a-completely-empty-inbox-can-be-suspicious-1\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-284183-problem-if-you-want-to-quickly-clean-up-sensitive-messages-either-sent-with-disappearing-messages-or-not-your-only-option-at-the-moment-is-to-manually-delete-individual-messages-or-delete-the-entire-thread-if-your-phone-is-inspected-a-completely-empty-inbox-can-be-suspicious-1\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Problem: If you want to quickly clean up sensitive messages (either sent with disappearing messages or not), your only option at the moment is to manually delete individual messages, or delete the entire thread. If your phone is inspected, a completely empty inbox can be suspicious.</h1>\n<h1><a name=\"p-284183-solution-what-people-actually-need-is-the-ability-to-batch-remove-specific-sensitive-messages-while-keeping-normal-conversation-intact-2\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-284183-solution-what-people-actually-need-is-the-ability-to-batch-remove-specific-sensitive-messages-while-keeping-normal-conversation-intact-2\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Solution: What people actually need is the ability to batch remove <em>specific</em> sensitive messages while keeping normal conversation intact.</h1>\n<h2><a name=\"p-284183-proposal-3\" class=\"anchor\" href=\"#p-284183-proposal-3\" aria-label=\"Heading link\"></a>Proposal:</h2>\n<p>Simple mark and delete:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Long-press a message → “Mark for deletion”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Small indicator shows it’s marked</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Mark as many messages as you want over time</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>When ready: conversation menu → “Delete marked messages”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Confirm → done</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
